<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000015#     2#          926#">Va. Code Ann. § 15.2-926</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_15.2-926"/><heading><desig>§ 15.2-926.</desig><title>Prohibiting loitering; frequenting amusements and curfew for minors; penalty</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a"/><heading><desig>A.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Any locality may by ordinance prohibit loitering in, upon or around any public place, whether on public or private property. Any locality may by ordinance also prohibit minors who are not attended by their parents from frequenting or being in public places, whether on public or private property, at such times, between 10:00 p.m. and 6:00 a.m., as the governing body deems proper.</p><p>A violation of such ordinances by a minor shall be disposed of as provided in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 16.1-278.4"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 16.1-278.4">§§ 16.1-278.4<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000016#     1#        278.4#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> and <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 16.1-278.5"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 16.1-278.5">16.1-278.5.<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000016#     1#        278.5#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation></p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b"/><heading><desig>B.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> A locality may by ordinance regulate the frequenting, playing in or loitering in public places of amusement by minors, and may prescribe punishment for violations of such ordinances not to exceed that prescribed for a Class 3 misdemeanor.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_c"/><heading><desig>C.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Without limiting or restricting the general powers created by this section, the term "public place" shall also include public libraries.</p></bodyText></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>Code 1950, § 15-8; 1954, c. 529; 1956, cc. 218, 664; 1956, Ex. Sess., c. 40; 1958, c. 279; 1960, c. 606; 1962, c. 623, § 15.1-514; 1968, c. 425; 1983, c. 502, § 15.1-33.4; <citation normalizedCite="1995 VA CH 59"><content><span normalizedCite="1995 Va. Ch. 59">1995, cc. 59<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1995#000059#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation normalizedCite="1995 VA CH 658"><content><span normalizedCite="1995 Va. Ch. 658">658<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1995#000658#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="1997 VA CH 587"><content><span normalizedCite="1997 Va. Ch. 587">1997, c. 587<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1997#000587#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="1998 VA CH 865"><content><span normalizedCite="1998 Va. Ch. 865">1998, c. 865<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1998#000865#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="1999 VA CH 1023"><content><span normalizedCite="1999 Va. Ch. 1023">1999, c. 1023<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue 